      "sha256": "796b709b53749d66fa20dada8aa6fdd9962d6fde342d511e9942184c001ac282",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "If we replace $2$ by $1$ then $A$ is a Sidon set, for which Erd\\H{o}s proved this is true."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "b506eee3e1213443291953d0ab9ef87b3f3e6298d319744d119522e88781e92a",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $A\\subset \\mathbb{N}$ be an infinite set such that, for any $n$, there are most $2$ solutions to $a+b=n$ with $a\\leq b$. Must\\[\\liminf_{N\\to\\infty}\\frac{\\lvert A\\cap \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert}{N^{1/2}}=0?\\]"
    }
  },
